  "description": "The autonomous shimmer mechanism fully engaged: macroCoupling at 0.85 activates independent sine-modulated amplitude flutter on upper partials 4-7, each offset by π/4 radians from its neighbors. Partials 4-7 boosted to 0.85-0.95 so the bioluminescent flutter is the primary sound, not an accent. Phi constant at depth 4 (8/5 = 1.6) places the upper partials in the overtone region where flicker is most audible. LFO2 at moderate rate rotates phase to reinforce the iridescence. No coupling partner required — the Nautilus generates its own light. Macros: COUPLING knob sweeps the bioluminescence depth in real time.",
